The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Sept. 4: Seven of the 10 plants of the Cement Corporation of India (CCI), for which players like Grasim and Dalmia have shown interest, will be sold. The proposal of the CCI and the department of heavy industry to sell the seven plants to raise funds for restructuring the company has received the nod of the Board for Reconstruction of Public Enterprises. The seven plants, which are not operating, will fetch Rs 617.76 crore. The BRPSE has also approved the closure of Bharat Opthalmic Glass.

 New Delhi, Sept. 4: Allianz wants to hike its stake from 26 per cent to 49 per cent in Bajaj Allianz General Insurance when the government raises the FDI cap in the sector, Bajaj Allianz CEO Kamesh Goyal said. Rahul Bajajs group has the majority 74 per cent stake in the venture.

 Chennai, Sept. 4: MRF Ltd may hike tyre prices soon because of a steep rise in raw material costs led by high rubber prices and spiralling oil rates, chairman and managing director K. M. Mammen said.

 New Delhi, Sept. 4: Charitable institutions, which do not attract income and corporate tax, have been exempted from the fringe benefit tax (FBT). 

 Mumbai, Sept 4: ONGC Videsh Ltd (OVL) has successfully completed the construction of the 741-km Sudan multi-product pipeline from Khartoum refinery to Sudan port export terminal two months ahead of schedule.




